Cardamom Cake with Brown Butter Frosting
  --Brooke Bell

Frosting:
1/2 c unsalted butter
16 oz package confectioners' sugar
1/3 c heavy whipping cream, room temp
1 tsp kosher salt

 In a medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Cook until butter turns a medium-brown color and has a nutty aroma, ~10 min. Remove from heat and let cool completely. In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, beat browned butter at medium-high speed until creamy, ~2 min. Gradually add confectioners' sugar, cream, and salt, beating until well combined, ~1 min. Set aside.

Cake:
3/4 c unsalted butter, softened
1 c sugar
4 large yolks, room temp
1/2 tsp almond extract
2 c ap flour
1 c sour cream, room temp
1 1/2 tsp ground cardamom
1/2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/4 kosher salt

Preheat oven to 350F; butter and flour 9" round cake pan.  In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar with a mixer at medium speed until fluffy, 3-4 min, stopping to scrape sides of bowl. Add yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add almond extract and beat for 30 s. Add flour, sour cream, cardamom, baking powder, baking soda, and salt, beating until smooth. Batter will be thick. Spread into prepared pan. Bake for 30 min. Cover with foil, and bake until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean, ~15 min more. Let cool in pan for 10 min; remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack. Using a serrated knife, cut cake in half horisontally. Spread frosting between layers and top of cake.
